'''Torbjørn Lysaker Heggem''' (born 12 January 1999) is a Norwegian [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Serie A]] club [[Bologna FC|Bologna]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]]. Primarily a [[centre-back]], Heggem can also play as a [[left-back]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Torbjørn Lysaker Heggem joined [[Rosenborg BK|Rosenborg]] in 2014 from Astor. He made his debut for Rosenborg coming on as a substitute against [[Lillestrøm SK|Lillestrøm]] in the [[2018 Mesterfinalen]].<ref name="mf-2018">{{cite web |url=https://www.nrk.no/sport/rosenborg-slo-lillestrom-i-mesterfinalen-1.14025383 |title=Hyller juniorene: – «Young boys» henter hjem et trofé til Rosenborg |website=NRK |date=26 April 2018 |access-date=17 April 2025 |language=no}}</ref> In January 2019, Heggem was sent out on loan to fellow [[Trondheim]] and [[Eliteserien]] club [[Ranheim Fotball|Ranheim]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ranheimfotball.no/nyheter/torbjorn-heggem-klar-for-ranheim |title=Torbjørn Heggem klar for Ranheim / Ranheim |publisher=Ranheimfotball.no |date=28 January 2019 |accessdate=2019-06-06 |language=no}}</ref> Later that year he made his debut in [[Eliteserien]] on 19 May, playing the full game which Ranheim won 3–1 away against [[Sarpsborg 08]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ranheimfotball.no/nyheter/disse-starter-mot-sarpsborg-08 |title=Disse starter mot Sarpsborg 08 / Ranheim |publisher=Ranheimfotball.no |date=2019-05-19 |accessdate=2019-06-06 |language=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ranheimfotball.no/nyheter/kruttsterk-prestasjon-i-sarpsborg |title=Kruttsterk prestasjon i Sarpsborg / Ranheim |publisher=Ranheimfotball.no |date=2019-05-19 |accessdate=2019-06-06 |language=no}}</ref> In January 2021 he joined [[Sandnes Ulf]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rbkweb.no/vis/15376|title =RBKweb - artikkel |website=Rosenborg BK |date=25 January 2021 |access-date=25 January 2021 |language=no}}</ref>

On 22 December 2022, Heggem signed for Swedish side [[IF Brommapojkarna]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bpfotboll.se/forening/valkommen-till-bp-torbjorn-lysaker-heggem/ |title=Välkommen till BP, Torbjørn Lysaker Heggem |website=IF Brommapojkarna |date=22 December 2022 |access-date=24 February 2025 |language=sv}}</ref>

===West Bromwich Albion===
On 4 July 2024, Heggem signed for [[EFL Championship]] side [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] on a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wba.co.uk/news/albion-complete-torbjorn-heggem-transfer |title=ALBION COMPLETE TORBJØRN HEGGEM TRANSFER |website=West Bromwich Albion |date=4 July 2024 |access-date=16 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c3g34m782l3o |title=West Brom sign Norwegian defender Heggem |website=BBC Sport |date=4 July 2024 |access-date=14 August 2025}}</ref> On 10 August 2024, he made his debut for the club in a 3–1 away win against [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|QPR]] in the opening league game, and assisted [[Josh Maja]]'s first goal in the first half.<ref>{{cite web|title=Queens Park Rangers 1–3 West Bromwich Albion |website=Sky Sports |date=10 August 2024|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/queens-park-rangers-vs-west-bromwich-albion/report/509351|access-date=12 August 2024}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 8 December 2024, scoring first in a 2–2 draw with [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cg5276qd5z4t |title=West Bromwich Albion 2–2 Sheffield United |website=BBC |publisher=BBC Sport |date=8 December 2024 |access-date=24 February 2025}}</ref> He won the [[2024–25 West Bromwich Albion F.C. season|2024–25]] West Bromwich Albion Player of the Season award for his performances during the campaign.<ref name="heggem-poty">{{cite web |url=https://www.wba.co.uk/news/albion-mens-202425-awards-winners |title=Albion Men's 2024/25 awards winners |website=West Bromwich Albion FC |date=14 April 2025 |access-date=15 April 2025}}</ref>

===Bologna===
On 15 August 2025, Heggem signed for [[Serie A]] club [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] for an undisclosed fee,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bolognafc.it/torbjorn-heggem-al-bologna/|trans-title=Torbjørn Heggem to Bologna|title=Torbjørn Heggem al Bologna|language=Italian|website=www.bolognafc.it|date=15 August 2025|accessdate=15 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wba.co.uk/news/torbjorn-heggem-signs-bologna|title=Torbjørn Heggem signs for Bologna|website=www.wba.co.uk|date=15 August 2025|accessdate=15 August 2025}}</ref> reported to be in the region of £10 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cnv7r0m8gl8o|title=West Brom defender Heggem completes Bologna move|publisher=BBC Sport|date=15 August 2025|accessdate=15 August 2025}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 30 August 2025, in a 1–0 win against [[Como 1907|Como]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/736794/como-bologna |title=Bologna 1–0 Como |website=ESPN |date=30 August 2025 |access-date=31 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Heggem received his first call-up to the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]] on 1 October 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wba.co.uk/news/torbjorn-heggem-earns-first-inclusion-senior-norway-squad |title=Torbjørn Heggem earns first inclusion in senior Norway squad |website=West Bromwich Albion F.C. |date=1 October 2024 |access-date=10 September 2025}}</ref> He made his debut for the Norway national team on 13 October 2024 in a [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League B|UEFA Nations League]] game against Austria at the [[Raiffeisen Arena (Linz)|Raiffeisen Arena]]. He substituted [[David Møller Wolfe]] in the 79th minute, as Austria won 5–1.<ref>{{cite web |website=ESPN |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698965/norway-austria|title=Austria v Norway game report |date=13 October 2024 |access-date=13 October 2024}}</ref>

